71
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:16,320
We belong to each other.

72
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:19,680
I never wanted to divorce you.

73
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,840
I knew...

74
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:27,520
that you didn’t want to divorce me, that you
wouldn’t back down out of sheer stubbornness.

75
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,120
Even if you had divorced me, I
would still have come after you.

76
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,960
No matter where you went, you
would never have escaped me.

77
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:38,200
Let’s rewrite those 187 days
from the beginning, Mercan.

78
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:41,920
What do you mean?

79
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,640
Let the 187th day be our wedding.

80
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,840
Come to me as my bride,
dressed in white that day.

81
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,080
This time, let’s look
at each other with love.

82
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,880
Let’s put ambition,
hatred, and anger aside...

83
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,280
and start over from the beginning.

84
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:04,760
Then let’s go far away
from everyone and everything.

85
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,920
With you, I’m ready for anything.

86
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:13,680
I would even go to the
other end of the world.

87
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,520
Don’t pull a long face right away.

88
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,120
I know what you’re thinking.

89
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,000
You bear no guilt in what happened.

90
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:52,560
I know, but I can’t help thinking about it.

91
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,200
I cannot imagine a
life without you, Mercan.

92
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,360
Neither can I.

93
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,840
What do you think they’ll say when
they learn we gave up on the divorce?

94
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:13,960
I’m so happy right now. I don’t care what
they think or what they say. Nothing matters.

95
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,680
It shouldn’t matter to you either.

96
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:19,200
But don’t worry, I’ll
take care of everything.

97
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,760
I won’t let anyone hurt you.

98
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,640
This time, we’ll overcome
everything together.

99
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,520
We’ll face every obstacle side by side.

100
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,680
Look at all we’ve been through.
We’ll get through the rest as well.

101
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:42,440
Or we run away. You kidnap me.

102
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:46,640
Fine. But first we’ll have our wedding.

103
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,480
So you’re determined about this wedding.

104
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,000
Of course.

105
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:55,440
You’re such a strange woman. Shouldn’t
you be the one insisting on this?

106
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,760
If it were up to me,
there’d be no need at all.

107
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,680
That won’t do.

108
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:07,080
Whatever I took from you,
I will give it all back.

109
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,720
Everything I deprived you of.

110
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,560
Everything will be done properly.

111
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,840
I need nothing in this world except you.

112
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,600
Nor do I.

113
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,720
Come on.

114
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,800
Let’s go shock everyone at the mansion
by telling them we’re not divorcing.

115
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,320
What if we told them later?

116
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:34,680
I mean... I want us
to be alone for a while.

117
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,320
Away from the mansion.

118
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,040
If we’re truly starting
everything from the beginning...

119
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,160
The place where you came into my life.

120
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,120
You were hiding among the nets.

121
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,760
As if no one would notice you.

122
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,320
But I thought I was hiding.

123
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,800
You were like a water
nymph caught in the nets.

124
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:42,920
You looked so delicate.

125
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:46,480
Now that I think about it,
you were quite gentle too.

126
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,000
I was a complete brute.

127
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,640
I’m sorry for everything.

128
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,800
You were my first love, Mercan.

129
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,920
As you tried to free yourself from
those nets, you were so beautiful...

130
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,520
My heart pounded like mad at that moment.

131
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,640
When I freed you from the
nets and lifted your veil...

132
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,520
In that moment I saw my
bride standing before me.

133
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,040
That was when we truly got married.

134
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,440
I wish you could see
yourself through my eyes.

135
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,960
We met again after years.

136
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,880
I was struck as if by lightning.

137
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,880
I used to watch you from afar, but...

138
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,960
That moment was different.

139
00:09:58,280 --> 00:10:00,200
When our eyes met...

140
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,720
you flowed straight into my heart...

141
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,400
and filled it completely.

142
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,320
There was an invisible bond between us.

143
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:19,320
I could neither break
that bond nor untangle it.

144
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,360
I was furious with myself.

145
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,320
And I punished you along with myself.

146
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,640
So... my anger and cruelty
always came from that.

147
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,160
For hurting you...

148
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,600
I’m sorry a thousand times over.

149
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:49,160
So all the torment you put me
through was because of love, is that it?

150
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,360
Yes.

151
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,760
Because I was angry with myself.

152
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:03,240
So what do you want to do?
Shall we sail out to sea?

153
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,120
Or something else?

154
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,880
No, the weather’s a bit cold.

155
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,040
But we could eat something.

156
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,640
Alright.

157
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,560
Let’s see how we can fill you up.

158
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:15,560
Come.

159
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,880
Look, Ismail Brother is here again.

160
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,520
Ismail Brother.

161
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,240
Oh, Ateş.

162
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,136
My friend, you’ve set the table again.

163
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,480
Welcome, youngsters. How are you?

164
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,560
We’re good, my friend. How are you?

165
00:11:40,561 --> 00:11:43,280
I’m good, maşallah. Business
was good today. Plenty of fish.

166
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,560
Got anything for us?

167
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,960
Yes, yes. The fish were good today.

168
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:48,600
Fish?

169
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,120
Let me treat you.

170
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,280
Sure, my friend. Two portions.

171
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,400
Alright.

172
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,160
One with lots of onions.

173
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,280
Oh, where’s the other bread?

174
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,720
Is it warm?

175
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:04,880
A little.

176
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,880
I think we shouldn’t go home.

177
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,480
Let’s run away.

178
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,680
Alright, alright.

179
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,120
My brave wife.

180
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:49,960
Come.

181
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,360
Yes, Mrs. Müzeyyen, you called for me.

182
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:55,960
Zehra, did Ateş return?

183
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:58,200
No, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

184
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,960
And Mrs. Mercan hasn’t returned yet either.

185
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:03,280
Perhaps the court session ran long.

186
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:06,720
They’re divorcing by mutual
consent. What could possibly take long?

187
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,040
They’re not answering their phones either.

188
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,600
Maybe they’re stuck in traffic.

189
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,000
I wish it were that simple.

190
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,320
Let me know the moment Ateş returns.

191
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,440
Alright, Mrs. Müzeyyen. Anything else?

192
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,720
No. Get back to your work.

193
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,080
Insallah what I fear won’t come to pass.

194
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,680
Insallah.

195
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,800
Where on earth did they disappear to?

196
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:56,520
Ateş isn’t answering his phone.

197
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,920
With everyone talking at once,
they must have felt overwhelmed.

198
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,240
That’s why they went alone.

199
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:03,840
They’re right.

200
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:08,400
And the irony is people with no
right to speak are talking the most.

201
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:10,840
Just think about it.

202
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:13,560
Even those who tried to kill
Mercan have the nerve to speak.

203
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,080
Where is Mercan, Demet?

204
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,080
They haven’t returned yet.

205
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,440
What do you mean they haven’t returned?

206
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,800
Didn’t you go together?

207
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:34,800
We were supposed to, but I think
they left without anyone seeing them.

208
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,480
I called Mercan, but she didn’t answer.

209
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,240
Ateş isn’t answering either.

210
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,080
Insallah nothing bad has happened.

211
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,560
Insallah.

212
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,400
Mercan?

213
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,040
Why did you go alone?

214
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,080
What’s going on?

215
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,880
What’s with the two of you?

216
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,640
We gave up on the divorce.

217
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,016
In fact, we’re having a wedding soon.

218
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,240
That’s what I’m talking about!

219
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,320
Son, thank God. I knew it.

220
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,040
I’m so happy.

221
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,560
Congratulations.

222
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:08,520
Finally, something good
will happen in this mansion.

223
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,560
I’ll be right back.

224
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:24,840
Don’t let it trouble you.

225
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:35,080
Mercan.

226
00:18:35,081 --> 00:18:36,400
Congratulations, my daughter.

227
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,800
Thank you, Mother.

228
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,360
How could you do this?

229
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:25,880
We started this road
together, and you cast me aside.

230
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:31,360
Mother Müzeyyen, you cared for
me, protected me, educated me.

231
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,040
I can never disregard that.

232
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,600
You were like both mother and father to me.

233
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,240
You know I have endless respect for you.

234
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,160
But Mercan is my wife.

235
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,800
And I expect her to be respected.

236
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,160
Respect for Haydar’s daughter, is that it?

237
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:48,920
This revenge wasn’t
only yours. It was ours.

238
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:51,880
That man shattered my family.

239
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,920
You know Mercan is innocent.

240
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,080
She has nothing to do with what happened.

241
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,120
You are my family.

242
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,320
Nothing will ever change that.

243
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:05,960
But I cannot forget what
was done to Mercan either.

244
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,480
Still, I want your consent.

245
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,400
Don’t worry.

246
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,880
Haydar will receive the
punishment he deserves.

247
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,160
Sooner or later.

248
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,000
But as I said before...

249
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:25,000
Mercan is my red line.

250
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:34,160
Insallah we can all become a family again.

251
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:41,040
No matter what I say, I
won’t change your mind, will I?

252
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:47,400
Meanwhile, your girl will
not stay in this mansion.

253
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:50,040
I want her gone as soon as possible.

254
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,480
Please give me a little more time, Ateş.

255
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,360
I promise I will send her away.

256
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:57,720
But if I send her now,
everything will get worse.

257
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,680
Don’t let it drag on too long.

258
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:05,960
I promise. Thank you, son.

259
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:14,560
It’s time to put an end to this.

260
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:28,680
That woman will raise hell. Be prepared.

261
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:34,480
Ateş will stand by his
love and overcome everything.

262
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:35,840
Don’t worry, my daughter.

263
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,840
Insallah without harm or trouble.

264
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:28,360
Kiss the hand, my girl.
Don’t you know your manners?

265
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,800
Since you’re not divorcing.

266
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:09,680
Mother, how could you do this... Mother?

267
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:46,040
Come on, my sister. Pick up the phone.

268
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,120
Brother.

269
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:57,640
Demet? Why aren’t you
answering your phone, my girl?

270
00:23:58,720 --> 00:24:01,520
I can’t speak with you while the
entire household is around me, can I?

271
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:06,440
Alright, Mercan returned.
Their marriage is over, right?

272
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:11,800
Demet?

273
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,240
They gave up on the divorce.

274
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:22,320
Didn’t you go to court with Mercan?

275
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:25,120
They left the house without telling anyone.

276
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,760
It surprised everyone at home as well.

277
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:29,720
Brother.

278
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:31,920
Accept it.

279
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,600
Forget Mercan.

280
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,960
Even if they had divorced, she
would never have been with you.

281
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:40,880
How many times have I told you
not to tell me this nonsense?

282
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,600
Enough...

283
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:52,280
I will never let Mercan be yours.

284
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:55,160
I would die...

285
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,080
I would die before I give her to you.

286
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:20,240
What did I tell you? Didn’t I say
not to worry, we’d handle everything?

287
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:24,560
They have to accept our marriage.

288
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:29,800
I’m still surprised.
How did you convince her?

289
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,640
This is love.

290
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:34,720
I said you can’t reason with love.

291
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,120
She eventually lowered her sails.

292
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:40,520
Of course you didn’t say it like that.

293
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:42,720
Something close to it.

294
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,120
Maybe even harsher.

295
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,320
I said Mercan is my red line.

296
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:51,360
Really?

297
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,480
Am I your red line?

298
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,400
Yes.

299
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:58,640
I drew the line like this.

300
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:00,640
Then I said, full stop.

301
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:04,680
I don’t know.

302
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:07,640
I’m still not sure she truly accepted it.

303
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:13,160
She will. She has to.

304
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:17,760
Mother Müzeyyen has suffered a lot.

305
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:21,680
But none of it was your fault.

306
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:27,880
Besides, by forgiving Aslı, you did
the greatest kindness you could for her.

307
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:36,560
Mother Müzeyyen won’t harm
you anymore. Don’t worry.

308
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:43,800
Don’t take this the wrong way, my lord,
but I stay on guard around your family.

309
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,160
What did you say?

310
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:50,320
You said “my lord” so nicely.

311
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:52,760
My lord.

312
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,400
My pearl, my Mercan.

313
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,160
My beloved heart.

314
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,640
My one and only.

315
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:14,400
My reason.

316
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,720
My soulmate.

317
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,800
Thank you, my Çiçek.

318
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:15,240
Bon appétit.

319
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:28,480
My girl, kiss the lady’s hand.

320
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,560
Mother, look at those
stares, for God’s sake.

321
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,120
Mom, what are you doing?

322
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,440
Malik.

323
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:55,920
If we had known you were coming, we would
have waited to make the formal proposal.

324
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:59,800
I wish you had informed us beforehand.

325
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:04,800
It seems today was destined.

326
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:16,120
You speak so beautifully. Just like us.

327
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:22,720
Mother Binnaz, my mother
lived here for a while before.

328
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:24,880
That’s why she knows Turkish fairly well.

329
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:32,040
Is that so? How nice.

330
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:44,120
My girl, go on, kiss Mrs. Ayşe’s hand.

331
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:48,800
Let me please.

332
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,280
Mother.

333
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,760
So how are you, Insallah?

334
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,040
We’re well.

335
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:17,560
We’re well

336
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,640
Malik, what are you
saying? This is shameful!

337
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,440
Alright, okay Mom.

338
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:33,280
We haven’t seen each other in
a long time. Let’s talk alone.

339
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,200
Of course, please go ahead.

340
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,240
I’ll just...

341
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:44,560
Son, take your mother’s phone with you too.

342
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:47,120
I’ll take it, Mother. Thank you.

343
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,880
Come, Mother.

344
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:04,000
Who was that woman?

345
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,240
Malik’s mother.

346
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,440
Mom, what are you doing?

347
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:29,120
This marriage is not happening!

348
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,320
Are you out of your mind?!

349
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,240
Just look at the place they live in.

350
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:35,680
Mom, just listen to me for a bit.

351
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:38,840
No. You will listen to me.

352
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:41,640
You’re not thinking about your father.

353
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:49,639
The son of a powerful man in business
and politics cannot marry a servant.

354
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:52,880
Mom, your voice... That's
enough, Mom, that's enough!!!

355
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:58,000
Look, I’ve made my decision.

356
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:02,640
I will marry her. I will
never give up on Çiçek.

357
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:07,800
Understand? and that
is my final word to you.

358
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:14,320
Besides, why did you come all the way here?

359
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:18,880
Why did you come all this
way? Just to say these things?

360
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,360
You could have said all this on the phone.

361
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:28,760
But no, you came all the way here just to
do what you did a moment ago, didn’t you?

362
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:35,360
You belittled those decent, honorable
people just because they are poor.

363
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,320
I wish you had never come, Mother.

364
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,360
I truly wish you had never come.

365
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:50,200
At least then I wouldn’t have gone through
that humiliating moment you just caused.

366
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:13,240
Hello.

367
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:23,560
He's not convinced. I can't
talk to him here. What do we do?

368
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,999
They won’t divorce and you accepted it.

369
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,320
You even had that girl kiss
your hand, didn’t you, Mother?

370
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:40,640
How could you do that?

371
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,680
Didn’t you think of me at all?

372
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,720
Ateş refuses to give up.

373
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:47,640
Mother, don’t.

374
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:51,400
Don’t talk to me about
Ateş’s love for that snake.

375
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,600
Mother... you’re plotting something
again, aren’t you? You have a plan.

376
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,920
That’s why you pretended
to accept that girl.

377
00:34:13,160 --> 00:34:15,760
You’ll put them in their
place like before, won’t you?

378
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:27,120
How? How could you accept this?

379
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:35,320
She’s the daughter of my father’s killer.

380
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,840
How can you accept this, Mother?

381
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:55,599
We have to accept it. We
must, if we want to keep Ateş.

382
00:34:55,600 --> 00:35:00,040
Mother, we’ve already lost Ateş.

383
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:04,040
Don’t you see? The man
says he will not divorce.

384
00:35:07,280 --> 00:35:09,640
Mother, that girl has him
wrapped around her finger.

385
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:13,160
She plays innocent in front of
Ateş. Am I the only one who sees this?

386
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,520
Aslı, that’s enough.

387
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:32,920
You have to accept it. Don’t
push your luck any further.

388
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:35,920
Let go of this obsession with Ateş.

389
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:38,960
You cannot force someone to love you.

390
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,960
Ateş doesn’t want you here anymore.

391
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:50,560
You need to leave as soon as possible.

392
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:11,280
What do you mean they won’t divorce,
Nermin? Has the girl lost her mind?

393
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,440
This is better, Haydar.

394
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:18,440
After everything Ateş did to me, my
daughter will stay married to that man?

395
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:21,320
They love each other.

396
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:24,480
Look... Ateş is madly in love with Mercan.

397
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:29,120
Despite everything, they
will continue their marriage.

398
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:36,560
Stand by your daughter for once.
Maybe she’ll forgive you too.

399
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:44,760
Haydar, you have caused
a lot of pain yourself.

400
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:49,240
You hurt them, and they came and hurt us.

401
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:52,840
For God’s sake, let
this blood feud end now.

402
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,880
Look, Mercan is all we have left.

403
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,360
Let her at least be happy
with the man she loves.

404
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:03,520
What are you saying, Nermin? What are you
saying? Can’t you see the state I’m in?

405
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:15,360
That man named Ateş will pay
for all of this. Do you understand?

406
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:26,800
I need to see Mercan.

407
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,040
Peace...

408
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,400
You’re wearing the necklace.

409
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:09,080
I had taken it off so it
wouldn’t remind me of you.

410
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:12,840
Did it work at least?

411
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:15,600
Does it look like it worked?

412
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:28,240
Something is missing here too.

413
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:30,680
Yes.

414
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,400
My ring.

415
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:41,000
I dropped it and
couldn’t find it afterward.

416
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:59,240
Where did you find it?

417
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:38,800
Never take this off again.

418
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:43,560
When I didn’t see it on you,
I took mine off out of anger.

419
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:48,600
I didn’t take it off. It fell, and I
kept it safe so it wouldn’t get lost.

420
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,480
All because of you.

421
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:57,320
If you act without listening or understanding, this is
what happens. Next time, ask me before throwing a tantrum.

422
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:03,400
I’d appreciate it if you reminded yourself of
that as well, Mr. Karahan. King of tantrums.

423
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:51,720
Mother.

424
00:40:54,080 --> 00:40:54,560
My daughter.

425
00:40:54,561 --> 00:40:56,200
What are you doing here?

426
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:58,960
I prepared the herbal tea you like.

427
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:04,520
The staff were nowhere
around, so I made it myself.

428
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:34,880
Go up to your room. I’ll come right away.

429
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:37,280
Thank you.

430
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:07,880
What is it?

431
00:42:08,640 --> 00:42:10,000
All the preparations are complete.

432
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:13,160
I did everything you told me.

433
00:42:18,520 --> 00:42:20,520
Ateş, I’m leaving.

434
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:25,560
For days you haven’t spoken to me about
anything but work. You won’t even look at me.

435
00:42:26,680 --> 00:42:27,720
And you’re right to do so.

436
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:32,360
As soon as I learned what Aslı
did... I should have come and told you.

437
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,760
I’m ashamed to face you.

438
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:42,800
Say something, Ateş.

439
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:46,440
Tell me I stabbed you in the back.

440
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,600
Tell me I betrayed you,
tell me I made a mistake.

441
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,480
Stand up and shout at me.

442
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:52,960
Just say something.

443
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:01,760
I understand you, brother.

444
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,040
It’s clear you won’t speak to me.

445
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:08,680
You must have your reasons.

446
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:14,760
May God watch over you.

447
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,200
Our road ends here.

448
00:43:17,640 --> 00:43:18,880
Take care of yourself, brother.

449
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:29,000
What you did...

450
00:43:29,280 --> 00:43:31,280
was not something I could swallow.

451
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:34,960
You’re right.

452
00:43:36,640 --> 00:43:37,400
You’re absolutely right.

453
00:43:37,401 --> 00:43:41,920
I have no defense against
you... what can I even say?

454
00:43:52,440 --> 00:43:54,080
You and I are like flesh and nail.

455
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:57,880
Closer than brothers.

456
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:02,600
And you’ve probably
already packed your bags.

457
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:04,800
I did.

458
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:07,960
Did you truly think I would send you away?

459
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:15,360
Drop the drama.

460
00:44:15,840 --> 00:44:16,880
It doesn’t suit you.

461
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:19,640
Besides, there’s a lot of work to do.

462
00:44:20,120 --> 00:44:22,680
And by the way, you’ll be my best man.

463
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:24,040
Keep that in mind.

464
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:26,040
There’s a celebration tonight.

465
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:27,400
You’re right.

466
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:29,840
A celebration without me
would be no celebration.

467
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:32,520
Do you think tonight’s
celebration will really happen?

468
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:35,960
It will.

469
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:41,000
Today...

470
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:43,520
everything will end.

471
00:45:28,400 --> 00:45:29,400
My love?

472
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:31,840
Yes?

473
00:45:33,840 --> 00:45:35,040
Did your mother say anything?

474
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,160
Did she like me?

475
00:45:40,120 --> 00:45:41,240
She didn’t like me, did she?

476
00:45:46,040 --> 00:45:47,440
Then again, the fault is mine.

477
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:48,760
Why am I even asking?

478
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:52,480
It was obvious she didn’t like me.

479
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:55,120
In fact, she hated both me and our home.

480
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,400
Alright.

481
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:06,720
Don’t be upset, Malik.

482
00:46:13,880 --> 00:46:15,640
My love... I mean...

483
00:46:16,120 --> 00:46:17,360
On behalf of my mother...

484
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:18,960
I’m so sorry.

485
00:46:20,440 --> 00:46:24,040
Seeing you hurt and upset like this...

486
00:46:25,000 --> 00:46:26,440
hurts me deeply.

487
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:28,800
What fault is yours in all this, Malik?

488
00:46:29,760 --> 00:46:33,440
Your mother isn’t at fault
either... she simply spoke her mind.

489
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:37,200
Listen to me.

490
00:46:39,720 --> 00:46:40,720
She will accept it.

491
00:46:41,680 --> 00:46:44,240
Sooner or later she will have
no choice but to accept it.

492
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:47,560
Because I chose to stand by you.

493
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:50,080
Because I love you so much.

494
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:54,920
Don’t be upset.

495
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:57,320
Don’t blame yourself.

496
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:01,600
We fell in love.

497
00:47:02,280 --> 00:47:04,200
We decided to marry together.

498
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:08,040
My love, there’s no
turning back from this road.

499
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:16,440
No one... absolutely
no one can separate us.

500
00:47:31,920 --> 00:47:33,920
Look what I brought you.

501
00:47:35,080 --> 00:47:38,760
Aww... You’re so sweet.
This is my favorite chocolate.

502
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:42,320
How do you get happy
over such small things?

503
00:47:44,080 --> 00:47:45,720
What else should I do but be happy?

504
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:52,440
The man I love is beside me,
and my favorite chocolate is here.

505
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:54,680
Isn’t that what happiness is?

506
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:24,800
No one in this world has
the power to separate us.

507
00:48:26,920 --> 00:48:27,920
I love you so much.

508
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:29,680
I love you too.

509
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:57,640
Thank you.

510
00:49:07,320 --> 00:49:09,760
Have you ever thought about
where we’ll go for our honeymoon?

511
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:13,800
Anywhere far from the mansion will do.

512
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,440
We’ll build a new world far from here.

513
00:49:20,720 --> 00:49:21,840
One that belongs only to us.

514
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:27,760
Our children will grow up in a
home filled only with memories of us.

515
00:49:32,360 --> 00:49:33,360
Yes.

516
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:37,920
They’ll grow up beside
us with love and trust.

517
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:43,440
Have you ever thought about it?

518
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:45,840
About what?

519
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:47,640
How many children we’ll have.

520
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:58,400
I never really thought about
it, but maybe two children.

521
00:49:59,320 --> 00:50:00,560
I want many children.

522
00:50:01,560 --> 00:50:03,760
A big, lively family.

523
00:50:05,160 --> 00:50:06,920
What exactly do you mean by big?

524
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:10,880
Maybe five.

525
00:50:11,360 --> 00:50:12,360
Five?

526
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:13,760
Maybe seven.

527
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:15,840
Only that many?

528
00:50:16,280 --> 00:50:18,240
Shall we start a football
team while we’re at it?

529
00:50:19,240 --> 00:50:20,920
Sure. Why not?

530
00:50:30,960 --> 00:50:31,960
What is it?

531
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,640
I’m very tense, Ateş.

532
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,240
And very sad as well.

533
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:45,680
I wish none of this had happened.

534
00:50:47,240 --> 00:50:49,240
I wish I had a normal family.

535
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:53,520
I wish this day would just end.

536
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:56,400
Don’t be sad.

537
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,040
It will end now.

538
00:50:59,640 --> 00:51:00,640
What’s done is done.

539
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:07,280
Promise me you’ll stay calm.

540
00:51:11,680 --> 00:51:12,760
Promise me.

541
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:18,240
I promise.

542
