552
00:52:12,200 --> 00:52:13,960
Did you know they weren’t going to divorce?

553
00:52:14,400 --> 00:52:16,360
What? They didn’t get divorced?

554
00:52:16,560 --> 00:52:18,360
For once in your life,
know something, Burak.

555
00:52:23,120 --> 00:52:25,240
This has nothing to do with you anyway.

556
00:52:25,520 --> 00:52:27,880
At worst Ateş goes to prison,
and Mercan ends up alone.

557
00:52:28,160 --> 00:52:31,040
There shouldn’t have been any
bond between them until now, Burak.

558
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:33,080
Do you understand?

559
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:35,640
Did you have the tip-off made?

560
00:52:37,240 --> 00:52:38,240
I did.

561
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:40,440
The police must have
stopped the trucks by now.

562
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:42,520
Soon they’ll head to the mansion too.

563
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:47,400
Let that Ateş walk out of that mansion in
handcuffs, and I’ll watch it with pleasure.

564
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:50,520
I already know what I’ll
do to him once he’s inside.

565
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:52,840
I did my part.

566
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:54,280
Our deal still stands, right?

567
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:56,920
Burak, my word is my bond.

568
00:53:01,280 --> 00:53:02,280
Alright.

569
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:04,360
See you.

570
00:53:05,960 --> 00:53:07,200
Hey idiot, where are you going?

571
00:53:16,160 --> 00:53:17,160
To the mansion?

572
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:29,080
What kind of people are
we doing business with?

573
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:34,080
Not long now, Mercan.

574
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:37,600
Not long until we’re reunited.

575
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:42,200
While Malik’s mother is here, we
should talk about this marriage matter.

576
00:53:42,440 --> 00:53:45,840
Whatever is going to happen, let it
happen properly and be done with it.

577
00:53:57,280 --> 00:53:58,640
Welcome, Mrs. Ayşe.

578
00:54:02,560 --> 00:54:05,280
Don’t get your hopes
up about this marriage.

579
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:14,880
This marriage will not happen.

580
00:54:19,080 --> 00:54:21,719
Don’t get carried away with pink dreams.

581
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:25,200
You and Malik will never happen.

582
00:54:30,840 --> 00:54:37,680
How shall I put it, you
belong to different worlds.

583
00:54:43,800 --> 00:54:49,640
I cannot understand how you
think yourself worthy of my son.

584
00:54:55,800 --> 00:55:02,600
That’s shameful. You cannot
come here and humiliate my sister.

585
00:55:03,800 --> 00:55:05,800
I said nothing wrong.

586
00:55:06,240 --> 00:55:07,680
One moment, one moment, Mrs. Ayşe.

587
00:55:08,720 --> 00:55:10,640
You cannot speak to my daughter like that.

588
00:55:10,840 --> 00:55:13,760
No one speaks to my children
in such a belittling way.

589
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:17,200
Who do you think you are? As if
you descend from Sultan Suleiman.

590
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:18,360
And what if you did?

591
00:55:18,680 --> 00:55:21,040
No one talks to my children like that.

592
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:23,240
I’m protecting my son.

593
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:24,760
And I’m protecting my daughter.

594
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:26,920
Alright, alright. Enough, Mother.

595
00:55:27,480 --> 00:55:28,960
This won’t solve anything. Calm down.

596
00:55:29,160 --> 00:55:30,160
What is going on here?

597
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:42,000
Mother, what are you doing here?

598
00:55:44,880 --> 00:55:46,480
Çiçek, what happened, my dear?

599
00:55:51,080 --> 00:55:52,280
What did you do to Çiçek?

600
00:55:53,200 --> 00:55:55,080
I didn’t do anything to Çiçek.

601
00:55:56,120 --> 00:56:00,120
I’m protecting you. I said
this marriage will not happen.

602
00:56:00,680 --> 00:56:03,320
How could you do such a thing?
What right do you have to say that?

603
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:15,520
I am your mother.

604
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:18,960
If you're my mom, treat me like a mom.

605
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:23,680
My Çiçek, look... don’t be upset.

606
00:56:27,880 --> 00:56:29,280
Malik.

607
00:56:29,800 --> 00:56:30,800
Mother, enough.

608
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:34,720
Please... be quiet.

609
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:14,680
Let’s talk for a moment.

610
00:58:16,840 --> 00:58:18,320
What is there to talk about with you?

611
00:58:18,560 --> 00:58:19,560
Sit down.

612
00:58:34,280 --> 00:58:36,000
I want Mercan to be happy from now on.

613
00:58:40,840 --> 00:58:43,080
The past must be completely closed.

614
00:58:45,560 --> 00:58:47,240
That’s why I want to talk one last time.

615
00:58:49,320 --> 00:58:51,360
At last you’ve found
the right path, Mr. Ateş.

616
00:58:52,640 --> 00:58:53,960
But you’re a little late.

617
00:58:55,560 --> 00:58:56,960
Late or early.

618
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:05,960
I want to learn how my
mother and father died.

619
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:10,960
What difference will knowing that make?

620
00:59:15,080 --> 00:59:16,680
I have the right to know.

621
00:59:17,920 --> 00:59:18,960
You owe me that.

622
00:59:21,360 --> 00:59:23,440
If I am going to open
a new page in my life...

623
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:28,240
nothing must remain hidden.

624
00:59:32,000 --> 00:59:35,479
Your father saw things he shouldn’t
have seen. Then the police...

625
00:59:35,480 --> 00:59:36,480
What did he see?

626
00:59:41,680 --> 00:59:43,360
We were smuggling migrants.

627
00:59:44,200 --> 00:59:46,600
They were never going to
reach their destinations anyway.

628
00:59:54,240 --> 00:59:56,599
Your father overheard the conversation.

629
00:59:56,600 --> 00:59:58,760
Then Rıza noticed him.

630
00:59:59,160 --> 01:00:00,560
An argument broke out between them.

631
01:00:02,840 --> 01:00:04,960
Rıza pulled out his gun to scare him.

632
01:00:08,320 --> 01:00:10,800
During the scuffle, when your
father tried to grab the gun...

633
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:13,880
the gun went off and the fight escalated.

634
01:00:21,760 --> 01:00:24,320
Then your mother ran outside
when she heard the gunshots.

635
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:27,960
In panic, Rıza shot your mother as well.

636
01:00:29,320 --> 01:00:31,120
I’m very tense, Ateş.

637
01:00:32,560 --> 01:00:33,560
And very sad.

638
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:40,000
I wish... none of this had happened.

639
01:00:41,640 --> 01:00:43,360
I wish I had a normal family.

640
01:00:48,320 --> 01:00:54,480
I wish this day would end...
Promise me you’ll stay calm.

641
01:01:01,920 --> 01:01:03,440
And you killed Rıza too.

642
01:01:04,680 --> 01:01:05,680
And Şahin...

643
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:13,520
I silenced those who needed to be silenced.

644
01:01:15,480 --> 01:01:17,920
You even killed your own
brother without blinking.

645
01:01:18,280 --> 01:01:20,280
How do I know you
didn’t kill my father too?

646
01:01:20,600 --> 01:01:21,600
Why should I believe you?

647
01:01:22,600 --> 01:01:24,440
You don’t have to believe me, Mr. Ateş.

648
01:01:29,240 --> 01:01:30,440
I’m telling you what happened.

649
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:34,440
Look... your father was a good man.

650
01:01:38,280 --> 01:01:39,760
Spare me the sentimental words.

651
01:01:39,960 --> 01:01:42,560
They don’t suit you.

652
01:01:44,560 --> 01:01:47,120
You put dozens of people on
boats and sent them to their deaths.

653
01:01:48,040 --> 01:01:51,000
You caused the deaths of dozens of people.

654
01:01:51,520 --> 01:01:53,400
They were desperate, hopeless people.

655
01:01:54,040 --> 01:01:56,160
They would have suffered
wherever they went anyway.

656
01:01:56,640 --> 01:01:58,520
We did nothing but a favor for them.

657
01:01:59,440 --> 01:02:00,920
Who do you think you are?

658
01:02:02,040 --> 01:02:05,560
Do you decide who lives and who dies?

659
01:02:05,760 --> 01:02:09,400
This world belongs to men who
have the power to decide, Ateş.

660
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:11,760
And I am one of those powerful men.

661
01:02:12,360 --> 01:02:14,200
Now I’m deciding your fate.

662
01:02:14,920 --> 01:02:17,600
Did you think I would watch you
marry my daughter and live happily?

663
01:02:22,160 --> 01:02:23,840
Your end has come as well, Mr. Ateş.

664
01:02:24,920 --> 01:02:26,440
I believe the police came for you.

665
01:02:27,720 --> 01:02:31,320
You can’t be naive enough to think I would
sit here and tell you everything like a fool.

666
01:02:32,840 --> 01:02:34,880
I told you because I knew
you were going to prison.

667
01:02:40,880 --> 01:02:42,000
Haydar Yıldırım.

668
01:02:46,360 --> 01:02:47,360
You are under arrest.

669
01:02:47,760 --> 01:02:50,320
Human trafficking and causing
death through premeditation.

670
01:02:50,480 --> 01:02:51,040
What is happening?

671
01:02:51,041 --> 01:02:52,080
Don’t resist!

672
01:02:52,360 --> 01:02:53,880
What are you talking about?

673
01:02:54,240 --> 01:02:55,240
I didn’t do anything.

674
01:02:56,160 --> 01:02:57,360
What are you doing?

675
01:02:58,200 --> 01:02:59,200
Let go!

676
01:03:11,800 --> 01:03:15,400
What we heard is enough to keep
him in prison for life, Mr. Ateş.

677
01:03:57,800 --> 01:03:59,959
Let go, I didn’t do anything, let go!

678
01:03:59,960 --> 01:04:00,960
Slander!

679
01:04:01,760 --> 01:04:03,520
I did nothing, it’s slander, let go!

680
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:05,080
I said let go!

681
01:04:07,320 --> 01:04:08,320
He set me up.

682
01:04:16,720 --> 01:04:18,680
You helped him set a trap for your father.

683
01:04:19,240 --> 01:04:21,640
You wanted that trap to
be set for your father.

684
01:04:22,240 --> 01:04:23,240
Let go!

685
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:31,640
I did nothing, I’m innocent.

686
01:04:31,960 --> 01:04:33,680
Where are you taking me? Let go!

687
01:04:33,880 --> 01:04:34,880
I said let go!

688
01:04:35,880 --> 01:04:36,880
Let me go!

689
01:04:37,560 --> 01:04:38,560
I’m innocent.

690
01:04:39,320 --> 01:04:40,560
You lied to me.

691
01:04:41,840 --> 01:04:42,840
You deceived your father.

692
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:44,480
You will answer for this.

693
01:04:45,520 --> 01:04:46,680
I’m innocent.

694
01:04:47,560 --> 01:04:49,000
You lied to me.

695
01:04:50,400 --> 01:04:52,600
All of you will answer for this.

696
01:04:53,040 --> 01:04:54,040
Let go!

697
01:04:58,800 --> 01:04:59,800
Take your hands off me!

698
01:05:01,400 --> 01:05:03,400
Let go, I did nothing, let go!

699
01:05:03,600 --> 01:05:04,600
Slander!

700
01:05:04,720 --> 01:05:06,959
You wanted the trap set for your father.

701
01:05:06,960 --> 01:05:08,200
Let go!

702
01:05:08,320 --> 01:05:10,120
I did nothing, I’m innocent.

703
01:05:10,320 --> 01:05:11,960
Where are you taking me? Let go!

704
01:05:47,560 --> 01:05:48,560
It’s over.

705
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:56,560
It’s over.

706
01:05:59,240 --> 01:06:03,240
Even if he is my father, no
crime should go unpunished.

707
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:11,520
Every time I place my hand in yours,
the wounds of my past fade a little more.

708
01:06:15,040 --> 01:06:16,720
Now there is only you and me.

709
01:07:12,360 --> 01:07:18,160
ONE WEEK LATER

710
01:07:52,640 --> 01:07:54,640
Good morning.

711
01:07:56,080 --> 01:07:58,080
Good morning.

712
01:08:03,640 --> 01:08:05,640
Is my beautiful wife awake?

713
01:08:07,120 --> 01:08:11,280
What’s this now? What’s gotten
into you, why are you so happy?

714
01:08:11,360 --> 01:08:15,960
Why shouldn’t I be happy? I woke up
to a beautiful day, my spirits are high.

715
01:08:16,040 --> 01:08:21,000
Above all, you’re by my
side. I’m a very lucky man.

716
01:08:22,760 --> 01:08:25,280
Is that the only thing
putting a smile on your face?

717
01:08:25,800 --> 01:08:29,240
Why? What else do I need to be happy?

718
01:08:30,720 --> 01:08:34,080
Come on, I’m starving like a wolf.
Get ready, let’s have our breakfast.

719
01:08:35,040 --> 01:08:36,040
Alright.

720
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:37,800
I’ll be waiting downstairs.

721
01:08:44,520 --> 01:08:46,520
Well, well...

722
01:08:48,040 --> 01:08:49,560
What on earth just happened to us?

723
01:09:22,880 --> 01:09:24,160
How are you?

724
01:09:25,080 --> 01:09:27,680
How can anyone be in a
place like this, Nermin?

725
01:09:28,200 --> 01:09:30,080
Just listen to the question you’re asking.

726
01:09:30,320 --> 01:09:37,120
Look, do you see now? Even that son of yours you trusted so
much joined forces with Ateş and had you thrown in prison.

727
01:09:39,640 --> 01:09:41,960
I will make him answer for that as well.

728
01:09:42,280 --> 01:09:44,800
Don’t worry.

729
01:09:45,040 --> 01:09:46,680
Just look at the state we’ve fallen into.

730
01:09:48,440 --> 01:09:50,640
At least you’re free, Nermin.

731
01:09:52,840 --> 01:09:54,200
Look at what I’m going through.

732
01:09:55,240 --> 01:09:57,880
The one week I’ve spent
behind bars felt like a year.

733
01:09:58,880 --> 01:10:01,000
Wherever I turn my head, there’s a wall.

734
01:10:05,400 --> 01:10:07,640
I feel like a rat trapped in a cage.

735
01:10:08,120 --> 01:10:09,520
I’m afraid of losing my mind.

736
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:14,760
I’m sorry, but you’re in
no position to blame anyone.

737
01:10:16,320 --> 01:10:18,240
If you ended up here, you are the reason.

738
01:10:19,960 --> 01:10:23,360
All the things you’ve done,
all the schemes you’ve run.

739
01:10:24,320 --> 01:10:27,800
You should have known one
day you would end up here.

740
01:10:28,560 --> 01:10:29,560
Well now.

741
01:10:30,360 --> 01:10:32,720
So you’re leaving the
whole blame on me, is that it?

742
01:10:36,840 --> 01:10:39,800
When you were living a life of luxury
thanks to me, everything was fine.

743
01:10:40,280 --> 01:10:42,080
Back then you didn’t
say a word, Mrs. Nermin.

744
01:10:43,520 --> 01:10:45,880
But the moment someone falls…

745
01:10:46,880 --> 01:10:49,360
Whatever I did, you were my partner in it.

746
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:53,080
Yet somehow I’m the
only one paying the price.

747
01:10:54,760 --> 01:10:57,240
But I will make Ateş
answer for all of this.

748
01:10:58,280 --> 01:11:01,080
I will make him pay
dearly for what he has done.

749
01:11:01,840 --> 01:11:04,080
And how exactly will you do that?

750
01:11:05,840 --> 01:11:08,240
Please be a little realistic, Haydar.

751
01:11:09,320 --> 01:11:12,200
As long as you are in prison,
doing such a thing is impossible.

752
01:11:16,280 --> 01:11:19,120
I think you should make
peace with your situation now.

753
01:11:20,680 --> 01:11:22,400
It might be easier to endure that way.

754
01:11:24,280 --> 01:11:25,280
Never!

755
01:11:25,480 --> 01:11:27,280
Never, Nermin. I will never accept it.

756
01:11:27,840 --> 01:11:29,360
I will never surrender.

757
01:11:35,520 --> 01:11:39,480
I won’t die before making
Ateş pay for what he did to me.

758
01:12:05,000 --> 01:12:06,000
There’s a placemat too.

759
01:12:06,160 --> 01:12:07,160
No need.

760
01:12:10,240 --> 01:12:12,080
Mother dear, that’s
buffalo yogurt, isn’t it?

761
01:12:12,920 --> 01:12:13,920
Yes, buffalo yogurt.

762
01:12:15,040 --> 01:12:16,680
As long as it’s there, let’s eat already.

763
01:12:17,840 --> 01:12:18,840
We will, son.

764
01:12:22,360 --> 01:12:23,360
Thank you, my dear.

765
01:12:26,200 --> 01:12:27,160
You went through the trouble, my dear wife.

766
01:12:27,161 --> 01:12:28,480
What trouble, my dear husband.

767
01:12:35,160 --> 01:12:36,160
Honey.

768
01:12:38,920 --> 01:12:41,920
You know, every time I think about
what happened to Mr. Haydar, I’m amazed.

769
01:12:42,040 --> 01:12:43,720
They handcuffed the man and took him away.

770
01:12:43,800 --> 01:12:45,680
Not even his wife said a word.

771
01:12:47,680 --> 01:12:51,600
Well, everyone reaps
what they sow in this life.

772
01:12:53,160 --> 01:12:55,520
Mr. Haydar caused the suffering
of many innocent people.

773
01:12:56,960 --> 01:12:58,840
My Mercan knows that.

774
01:12:59,360 --> 01:13:02,280
That’s why even though he is
her father, she won’t forgive him.

775
01:13:04,960 --> 01:13:08,960
Because my Mercan has a
conscience, she is fair.

776
01:13:10,520 --> 01:13:11,520
Of course she is.

777
01:13:12,400 --> 01:13:13,640
The man is guilty after all.

778
01:13:14,640 --> 01:13:19,720
And Mercan knows what
Mr. Haydar did to Ateş’s family.

779
01:13:20,800 --> 01:13:26,000
Even if it is her father, she would never excuse
someone who did that to the family of the man she loves.

780
01:13:26,480 --> 01:13:26,760
That’s right.

781
01:13:27,120 --> 01:13:29,920
Besides, Mercan has now
set out on a path with Ateş.

782
01:13:31,280 --> 01:13:33,520
From now on, Ateş is her family.

783
01:13:40,440 --> 01:13:42,880
Insallah the same will happen
for you and Malik, my daughter.

784
01:13:44,280 --> 01:13:45,320
Amen, mother.

785
01:13:46,440 --> 01:13:52,440
Though with the way his mother reacted,
our situation may be a little difficult.

786
01:13:55,440 --> 01:13:59,200
Oh dear. If only you had
let me deal with that woman.

787
01:14:03,640 --> 01:14:05,280
What was that? Who does she think she is?

788
01:14:05,400 --> 01:14:09,360
No one talks to my daughter
like that, looking down on her.

789
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:15,440
Whoever does such a thing to my daughter, I
will measure their forehead, mark my words.

790
01:14:17,960 --> 01:14:20,240
Well, that might be difficult, mother dear.

791
01:14:25,600 --> 01:14:28,280
The moment I looked at that
woman’s face, I understood.

792
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:29,800
She’s someone you’d fear crossing.

793
01:14:36,480 --> 01:14:37,880
Of course you would understand.

794
01:14:38,960 --> 01:14:40,040
After all, you’re the same.

795
01:14:46,920 --> 01:14:49,800
The two ends of the same
stick, the both of you.

796
01:14:54,080 --> 01:14:58,560
Look at you, always waiting
for a chance to throw a jab at me.

797
01:15:00,920 --> 01:15:04,360
Somehow the subject circles back
to me again, Lord give me patience.

798
01:15:05,160 --> 01:15:06,160
Çiçek.

799
01:15:15,160 --> 01:15:16,600
I didn’t keep you waiting, did I?

800
01:15:18,040 --> 01:15:19,040
You didn’t.

801
01:15:19,880 --> 01:15:21,840
Even if you had, it
wouldn’t have been a problem.

802
01:15:23,200 --> 01:15:25,560
So if I hadn’t come at all,
that would have been fine too?

803
01:15:25,680 --> 01:15:26,680
Is that what you mean?

804
01:15:27,640 --> 01:15:31,480
No. I only meant I would have waited.

805
01:15:35,280 --> 01:15:38,680
Shall we start breakfast
before I starve to death?

806
01:15:42,400 --> 01:15:43,400
Thank you.

807
01:15:43,840 --> 01:15:44,840
Enjoy your meal.

808
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:02,080
We have an appointment with
the event company tonight.

809
01:16:02,800 --> 01:16:05,120
We’ll talk about the table
arrangements and other details.

810
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:12,560
Don’t tell me you forgot.

811
01:16:14,800 --> 01:16:15,800
I didn’t forget.

812
01:16:16,480 --> 01:16:19,840
But we need to postpone it. I
don’t have time for it right now.

813
01:16:20,520 --> 01:16:21,760
I have a more important matter.

814
01:16:22,680 --> 01:16:24,680
But we agreed to go today.

815
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:28,360
We even arranged it according to your
schedule. Where did this come from now?

816
01:16:28,960 --> 01:16:31,920
I know, I would have liked to. But
like I said, I cannot postpone it.

817
01:16:32,160 --> 01:16:33,160
It’s very important.

818
01:16:35,400 --> 01:16:38,919
What could be so important,
I wonder? I’m truly curious.

819
01:16:38,920 --> 01:16:42,520
Did it come up at the last minute?
Because I know nothing about it.

820
01:16:42,960 --> 01:16:46,800
I’m in a bit of a hurry. I need to settle this
matter with Cemal. I’ll be back in a few hours.

821
01:16:48,120 --> 01:16:49,120
Goodbye.

822
01:16:52,280 --> 01:16:54,080
Why are you acting so mysterious?

823
01:16:55,360 --> 01:16:57,000
Weren’t you the one who wanted a wedding?

824
01:17:14,640 --> 01:17:18,880
Mom, you have to apologize to
Ms. Binnaz. What you did was wrong.

825
01:17:24,640 --> 01:17:28,120
And why should I apologize? For
your servant to talk to me like that?

826
01:17:29,000 --> 01:17:31,840
So what if she's a
servant and I'm a driver?

827
01:17:32,280 --> 01:17:35,920
You chose that for yourself, I'll pity you.

828
01:17:36,560 --> 01:17:44,160
People who work hard like that... Çiçek and I
are comfortable. Why are you talking like that?

829
01:17:44,240 --> 01:17:47,680
Everyone will know their
place and their limits.

830
01:17:48,800 --> 01:17:53,960
My place and limits, Mom? And who sets
these limits? Let me tell you something,

831
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:58,400
not everyone loses for money,
some people choose happiness.

832
01:18:01,720 --> 01:18:07,400
Çiçek and I are going to get married and I'm not
leaving her no matter what, do you understand me?

833
01:18:07,520 --> 01:18:08,520
I...

834
01:18:08,720 --> 01:18:11,320
I’m certain what I did was right.

835
01:18:12,160 --> 01:18:15,880
Nothing will change my mind.

836
01:18:19,760 --> 01:18:22,520
Then there is no point in
staying here any longer, Mother.

837
01:18:27,440 --> 01:18:28,440
Return to Egypt.

838
01:18:43,200 --> 01:18:44,200
Hello.

839
01:18:53,040 --> 01:18:54,040
What happened?

840
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:57,200
What did you talk about?

841
01:19:17,040 --> 01:19:19,880
Oh my, I’m drenched in sweat
from all this running around.

842
01:19:22,720 --> 01:19:24,720
What’s the matter,
son? Did a storm hit you?

843
01:19:29,360 --> 01:19:30,400
No.

844
01:19:31,040 --> 01:19:33,080
Your ships sank in the Black Sea.

845
01:19:36,120 --> 01:19:37,440
Something like that, mother dear.

846
01:19:39,480 --> 01:19:40,480
What happened?

847
01:19:40,880 --> 01:19:43,320
I got a little upset
about the child matter.

848
01:19:45,680 --> 01:19:47,160
Son, slow down.

849
01:19:47,480 --> 01:19:48,639
You just got married.

850
01:19:48,640 --> 01:19:52,600
First get to know each
other. Warm up to one another.

851
01:19:53,520 --> 01:19:56,760
It will happen eventually. It’s not
such a big issue, the matter of children.

852
01:20:02,640 --> 01:20:06,200
Mother dear... when my
father abandoned us...

853
01:20:08,000 --> 01:20:09,880
I made a promise to myself.

854
01:20:11,920 --> 01:20:14,640
One day I would build a very big family.

855
01:20:16,880 --> 01:20:18,920
I said I would never leave
my wife and my children.

856
01:20:21,600 --> 01:20:23,320
It seems that family won’t happen for me.

857
01:20:27,160 --> 01:20:28,160
Now hold on, son.

858
01:20:29,640 --> 01:20:32,120
Yesterday was one day, today is the second.

859
01:20:33,520 --> 01:20:36,880
It will happen. Everything
will fall into place.

860
01:20:37,400 --> 01:20:39,760
There will be children
too. Don’t trouble yourself.

861
01:20:45,800 --> 01:20:47,560
Insallah, mother dear, Insallah.

862
01:20:49,800 --> 01:20:51,080
My brave boy.

863
01:21:02,160 --> 01:21:06,480
Your wedding is near, yet there isn’t
the slightest sign of excitement in you.

864
01:21:07,400 --> 01:21:10,000
You’re troubled again.
Is it the same matter?

865
01:21:14,880 --> 01:21:19,760
I don’t know, Demet. After everything
that happened, it feels strange.

866
01:21:21,520 --> 01:21:25,160
I try not to think about it, but... from
time to time my mind drifts back to it.

867
01:21:26,440 --> 01:21:28,440
I keep wishing things had been different.

868
01:21:30,040 --> 01:21:31,040
You’re right.

869
01:21:31,760 --> 01:21:35,160
Because of what your father did,
you went through very hard times.

870
01:21:35,920 --> 01:21:37,400
But time will heal you.

871
01:21:40,520 --> 01:21:44,880
Shall we look at the invitation samples
together? You can give me your opinion too.

872
01:21:46,120 --> 01:21:47,880
Weren’t you going to
look at them with Ateş?

873
01:21:49,400 --> 01:21:52,320
We were, but he said he had work and left.

874
01:21:53,680 --> 01:21:55,640
His behavior was very strange today.

875
01:21:57,280 --> 01:21:58,960
Could it be because of wedding excitement?

876
01:22:00,480 --> 01:22:03,200
No. Something else is going on.

877
01:22:03,800 --> 01:22:05,279
If it were wedding excitement...

878
01:22:05,280 --> 01:22:08,640
he wouldn’t have canceled our
appointment with the event company tonight.

879
01:22:09,480 --> 01:22:11,120
He acts as if he’s hiding something.

880
01:22:12,440 --> 01:22:13,480
What do you mean?

881
01:22:15,000 --> 01:22:19,279
I woke up this morning... and
there he was in front of the mirror...

882
01:22:19,280 --> 01:22:22,080
fully dressed up, whistling.

883
01:22:23,520 --> 01:22:25,280
Then he said he had a
very important matter.

884
01:22:25,680 --> 01:22:26,680
He rushed out in a hurry.

885
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:33,840
Maybe he had work, who knows...
You’re a little tense too.

886
01:22:34,080 --> 01:22:35,120
Maybe you misunderstood.

887
01:22:36,880 --> 01:22:38,200
Maybe.

888
01:22:39,120 --> 01:22:40,960
Something doesn’t sit right with me.

889
01:22:41,880 --> 01:22:43,519
This wedding business...

890
01:22:43,520 --> 01:22:44,520
has me on edge.

891
01:22:45,680 --> 01:22:47,760
I keep thinking there
was no need for all this.

892
01:22:48,840 --> 01:22:50,240
And I end up taking it out on Ateş.

893
01:22:52,240 --> 01:22:55,640
But I like the excitement as well.

894
01:22:56,520 --> 01:22:57,560
I don’t know, Demet.

895
01:22:57,840 --> 01:23:00,000
I’m very confused these days.

896
01:23:00,880 --> 01:23:01,880
You’re right.

897
01:23:02,640 --> 01:23:04,440
You both went through difficult things.

898
01:23:07,640 --> 01:23:10,440
Look... whatever Ateş is
doing will come out eventually.

899
01:23:11,160 --> 01:23:12,360
Focus on your wedding.

900
01:23:13,200 --> 01:23:16,120
What did you do about the
wedding dress? Tell me that first.

901
01:23:16,760 --> 01:23:18,479
Wait, let me show you the ones I liked.

902
01:23:18,480 --> 01:23:19,480
Show me.

903
01:23:21,400 --> 01:23:23,280
I liked this one very much.

904
01:23:24,240 --> 01:23:25,960
This is beautiful.

905
01:23:26,120 --> 01:23:27,200
I love the veil.

906
01:23:27,440 --> 01:23:29,000
This is the third one.

907
01:23:29,200 --> 01:23:30,200
I liked this one too.

908
01:23:31,280 --> 01:23:33,120
No wonder you’re confused.

909
01:23:33,400 --> 01:23:34,480
They’re all beautiful.

910
01:23:35,720 --> 01:23:38,240
Ateş did well insisting on this wedding.

911
01:23:40,200 --> 01:23:42,120
Honestly, I didn’t think it was necessary.

912
01:23:42,400 --> 01:23:45,840
I wasn’t that eager, but since
he wanted it... he did it for me.

913
01:23:46,600 --> 01:23:48,200
Of course he did.

914
01:23:48,320 --> 01:23:48,960
Absolutely.

915
01:23:49,320 --> 01:23:50,360
Oh come on, Demet.

916
01:23:51,520 --> 01:23:52,600
Don’t get upset so quickly.

917
01:23:53,280 --> 01:23:55,560
You deserve to experience these things.

918
01:23:56,120 --> 01:23:57,440
Enjoy these days.

919
01:23:58,800 --> 01:24:01,600
I think Ateş’s idea of a wedding
is important for that reason.

920
01:24:03,040 --> 01:24:04,680
I want you to be happy.

921
01:24:07,960 --> 01:24:10,200
Anyway, forget all that for now.

922
01:24:10,520 --> 01:24:11,560
Tell me about you instead.

923
01:24:12,360 --> 01:24:13,720
Tell me about Cemal.

924
01:24:16,240 --> 01:24:17,880
Was I that obvious?

925
01:24:20,400 --> 01:24:23,040
There’s nothing to tell really.

926
01:24:24,680 --> 01:24:26,560
Cemal isn’t involved
in those kinds of matters.

927
01:24:28,120 --> 01:24:31,640
I don’t think anything beyond
friendship will happen between us.

928
01:24:33,640 --> 01:24:35,480
I don’t think you should
lose hope so quickly.

929
01:24:36,440 --> 01:24:38,200
Cemal went through difficult times too.

930
01:24:39,240 --> 01:24:41,200
Maybe he needs time.

931
01:24:45,640 --> 01:24:47,160
Don’t let your tea get cold.

932
01:25:20,080 --> 01:25:23,560
Everything I do is for
your own good, my daughter.

933
01:25:44,880 --> 01:25:47,320
Something feels strange
about me lately, Mother.

934
01:25:49,120 --> 01:25:50,200
I feel dazed.

935
01:25:51,280 --> 01:25:52,960
I don’t understand what’s happening to me.

936
01:25:55,000 --> 01:25:56,960
You will be well, my beautiful daughter.

937
01:25:57,640 --> 01:25:58,640
Don’t worry.

938
01:26:04,080 --> 01:26:05,760
I can’t endure it anymore, Mother.

939
01:26:06,840 --> 01:26:08,279
Please help me.

940
01:26:08,280 --> 01:26:12,160
It’s as if there’s a fog inside my head.

941
01:26:15,760 --> 01:26:17,216
Forget it, don’t think about these things.

942
01:26:17,240 --> 01:26:18,800
It’s better for you this way.

943
01:26:20,640 --> 01:26:23,000
Just as the body grows tired,
the mind grows tired too.

944
01:26:24,280 --> 01:26:26,840
See this as an opportunity
to clear your mind.

945
01:26:30,640 --> 01:26:31,960
Alright, I’ll try.

946
01:26:36,960 --> 01:26:37,960
How is Ateş?

947
01:26:38,800 --> 01:26:40,200
Is he still angry with me?

948
01:26:40,800 --> 01:26:41,879
Forget about Ateş.

949
01:26:41,880 --> 01:26:44,040
Think about yourself.

950
01:26:47,920 --> 01:26:48,920
You’re cold.

951
01:26:49,600 --> 01:26:52,800
Come inside, I’ll make you
some herbal tea to warm you up.

952
01:26:53,680 --> 01:26:55,760
Come on, my girl.

953
01:27:00,480 --> 01:27:01,480
Sit down, my daughter.

954
01:27:02,240 --> 01:27:03,560
Sit down, my beautiful daughter.

955
01:27:22,440 --> 01:27:25,120
Once you settle the wedding dress
matter, be sure to let me know.

956
01:27:25,560 --> 01:27:26,560
Alright.

957
01:27:26,760 --> 01:27:28,399
I need to choose one as
soon as possible anyway.

958
01:27:28,400 --> 01:27:31,360
Otherwise the bride will
show up without a dress.

959
01:27:32,080 --> 01:27:34,599
After seeing that black wedding dress...

960
01:27:34,600 --> 01:27:36,360
Don’t even ask.

961
01:27:46,920 --> 01:27:50,040
I wonder what those two
are discussing so intensely.

962
01:27:51,240 --> 01:27:52,440
Work, what else would it be?

963
01:27:58,640 --> 01:27:59,720
They’re coming.

964
01:28:04,080 --> 01:28:05,080
Hello.

965
01:28:05,200 --> 01:28:06,200
Hello.
Welcome.

966
01:28:07,840 --> 01:28:08,840
You are welcome as well.

967
01:28:10,560 --> 01:28:11,840
Glad to be here.

968
01:28:12,800 --> 01:28:15,000
I have matters at the company.

969
01:28:15,240 --> 01:28:16,400
I was on my way there anyway.

970
01:28:16,440 --> 01:28:18,000
I was about to head to the company too.

971
01:28:18,080 --> 01:28:19,120
Shall I give you a ride?

972
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:21,000
No need.

973
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:22,600
I’ll go myself.

974
01:28:22,840 --> 01:28:23,840
Don’t trouble yourself.

975
01:28:24,400 --> 01:28:27,240
My girl, I’m offering.
What trouble could there be?

976
01:28:28,120 --> 01:28:29,199
We’re going to the same place anyway.

977
01:28:29,200 --> 01:28:30,280
What trouble could that be?

978
01:28:30,360 --> 01:28:31,520
Let me at least do that much.

979
01:28:31,960 --> 01:28:32,960
Alright.

980
01:28:33,360 --> 01:28:34,639
You certainly complained a lot.

981
01:28:34,640 --> 01:28:36,896
I only said it out of politeness,
but that was my mistake.

982
01:28:36,920 --> 01:28:38,400
Look who I’m trying to be polite to.

983
01:28:38,520 --> 01:28:40,040
Fine, from now on you won’t be polite.

984
01:28:40,160 --> 01:28:42,000
I’m not exactly known
for being polite either.

985
01:28:42,720 --> 01:28:44,240
You’re still saying that.

986
01:28:44,840 --> 01:28:45,160
Fine.

987
01:28:45,720 --> 01:28:48,440
Let’s forget the last
five minutes, alright?

988
01:28:48,640 --> 01:28:50,280
No more politeness from now on.

989
01:28:50,480 --> 01:28:52,280
Alright, the last five
minutes are forgotten.

990
01:28:52,400 --> 01:28:53,720
Go ahead, lead the way. Let’s go.

991
01:28:54,200 --> 01:28:55,520
I’m already going.

992
01:28:57,160 --> 01:28:58,160
See you.

993
01:29:02,960 --> 01:29:04,520
Were we like that too?

994
01:29:05,600 --> 01:29:06,600
We still are.

995
01:29:09,080 --> 01:29:10,080
Insallah for the best.

996
01:29:11,760 --> 01:29:13,680
Come on, let me pour you some tea.

997
01:29:32,000 --> 01:29:36,440
Mom, look, this is the first time in
my life I'm asking you for something.

998
01:29:37,040 --> 01:29:40,040
Please, stop being stubborn.

999
01:29:40,120 --> 01:29:42,000
Look at yourself and look at her.

1000
01:29:42,080 --> 01:29:43,640
Mom,

1001
01:29:46,240 --> 01:29:47,720
you don't talk like that!

1002
01:29:47,800 --> 01:29:49,680
This marriage won't happen!

1003
01:29:49,800 --> 01:29:52,360
This marriage won't happen!

1004
01:30:02,760 --> 01:30:05,040
I didn’t understand what
you were talking about but...

1005
01:30:05,800 --> 01:30:08,160
it didn’t look like a
pleasant conversation.

1006
01:30:11,120 --> 01:30:12,760
Never mind, don’t upset yourself.

1007
01:30:15,120 --> 01:30:16,760
That’s not what saddens me.

1008
01:30:18,720 --> 01:30:22,520
What saddens me is that nothing
has changed after all this time.

1009
01:30:23,800 --> 01:30:26,040
They were always like
this. They never surprise me.

1010
01:30:27,680 --> 01:30:30,720
In our house there was always
talk of work, money, power.

1011
01:30:31,960 --> 01:30:36,280
I was always alone. It was as if a
wall stood between me and my family.

1012
01:30:37,120 --> 01:30:42,000
Cold breakfasts, dinners that
ended without a single word.

1013
01:30:43,800 --> 01:30:47,000
Companies are more important
to my father than his own child.

1014
01:30:48,200 --> 01:30:51,960
If they could, they would
probably buy love with money.

1015
01:30:52,560 --> 01:30:53,800
Just like they always do.

1016
01:30:56,120 --> 01:30:57,800
Once again they left me all alone.

1017
01:30:59,400 --> 01:31:01,399
Everyone has their own way of loving.

1018
01:31:01,400 --> 01:31:05,640
If they didn’t love you, would your
mother come all the way here for you?

1019
01:31:07,520 --> 01:31:10,360
I wish they could see
the beauty of your heart.

1020
01:31:11,160 --> 01:31:13,440
And stop saying you are all alone.

1021
01:31:13,720 --> 01:31:17,480
You’re not alone. You
have a big family here.

1022
01:31:18,000 --> 01:31:19,360
And they love you very much.

1023
01:31:21,880 --> 01:31:27,560
Çiçek, I learned what family
truly means here with all of you.

1024
01:31:28,280 --> 01:31:30,000
I saw the warmth of a family here.

1025
01:31:30,760 --> 01:31:32,720
I don’t want to lose that again.

1026
01:31:33,360 --> 01:31:34,360
You won’t lose it.

1027
01:31:56,800 --> 01:32:02,200
So, did you manage to settle that
very important matter with Cemal?

1028
01:32:03,160 --> 01:32:07,360
Yes, we did. Only a few small issues
remain. They will be settled tonight.

1029
01:32:09,200 --> 01:32:10,920
Is that the only thing you’re going to say?

1030
01:32:11,440 --> 01:32:14,920
I answered your question.
What else do you want me to say?

1031
01:32:15,840 --> 01:32:18,080
Nothing. Nothing at all.

1032
01:32:20,160 --> 01:32:24,800
Since you won’t be home tonight,
let’s at least handle the invitations now.

1033
01:32:26,200 --> 01:32:29,320
Alright, since you want it.

1034
01:32:31,280 --> 01:32:32,840
Since I want it?

1035
01:32:33,920 --> 01:32:37,599
Let me remind you, you were
the one who wanted this wedding.

1036
01:32:37,600 --> 01:32:40,040
If you recall, I wasn’t
that eager about it.

1037
01:32:40,480 --> 01:32:41,480
Well...

1038
01:32:42,480 --> 01:32:46,520
Alright, I know. But I wanted
you involved in the details.

1039
01:32:46,920 --> 01:32:48,480
So you would have a hand in every step.

1040
01:32:49,280 --> 01:32:53,400
Alright, but there are important
decisions we need to make together.

1041
01:32:53,840 --> 01:32:58,599
Yet you keep leaving. Tell me
about this important matter of yours.

1042
01:32:58,600 --> 01:33:00,320
I’m truly curious what it is.

1043
01:33:00,760 --> 01:33:02,120
Don’t exaggerate.

1044
01:33:12,600 --> 01:33:13,360
What are you doing?

1045
01:33:13,560 --> 01:33:17,040
I’m confiscating your phone. You won’t
get it back until you answer me properly.

1046
01:33:17,560 --> 01:33:18,120
Give me that phone.

1047
01:33:18,121 --> 01:33:19,640
I said give it.

1048
01:33:20,880 --> 01:33:21,440
I won’t.

1049
01:33:21,520 --> 01:33:22,520
Give me the phone.

1050
01:33:23,640 --> 01:33:24,920
I said I won’t.

1051
01:33:36,200 --> 01:33:37,480
Do you think you can escape?

1052
01:33:38,840 --> 01:33:40,080
Catch me if you can.

1053
01:33:40,400 --> 01:33:41,880
You think you can run away from me?

1054
01:33:47,120 --> 01:33:48,920
Catch me if you can.

1055
01:33:54,040 --> 01:33:55,600
Did you think you could escape from me?

1056
01:33:56,280 --> 01:33:58,480
Well done. Did that satisfy you?

1057
01:33:58,960 --> 01:33:59,960
It did.

1058
01:34:00,560 --> 01:34:02,520
You enjoy provoking me, don’t you?

1059
01:34:03,040 --> 01:34:04,040
Very much.

1060
01:34:04,760 --> 01:34:06,360
You shouldn’t be so arrogant.

1061
01:34:06,920 --> 01:34:09,720
Maybe you didn’t catch me.
Maybe I chose to be caught.

1062
01:34:10,600 --> 01:34:12,720
You can only escape from
me as long as I allow it.

1063
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:14,520
Remember that.

1064
01:34:15,360 --> 01:34:16,920
You can’t accept defeat, can you?

1065
01:34:17,760 --> 01:34:19,120
Oh that stubbornness of yours.

1066
01:34:20,280 --> 01:34:21,880
What about your stubbornness?

1067
01:34:23,360 --> 01:34:24,920
You still haven’t answered my question.

1068
01:34:25,640 --> 01:34:27,560
But I will find out eventually.

1069
01:34:28,480 --> 01:34:29,480
That might be difficult.

1070
01:34:30,040 --> 01:34:32,880
If I don’t want you
to... you won’t learn it.

1071
01:34:43,360 --> 01:34:44,400
Yes, Mrs. Sibel.

1072
01:34:45,880 --> 01:34:46,880
Sibel?

1073
01:34:49,400 --> 01:34:50,400
Yes.

1074
01:35:00,520 --> 01:35:01,520
Yes.

1075
01:35:06,360 --> 01:35:07,560
Who is this Mrs. Sibel?

1076
01:35:08,520 --> 01:35:09,520
So it’s Mrs. Sibel.

1077
01:35:31,120 --> 01:35:33,280
I wonder how our two are doing.

1078
01:35:33,800 --> 01:35:34,800
Our two?

1079
01:35:35,000 --> 01:35:36,000
Ateş and Mercan?

1080
01:35:37,720 --> 01:35:40,720
Mercan thinks Ateş is acting mysteriously.

1081
01:35:41,840 --> 01:35:43,840
And when she asked him, she got no answer.

1082
01:35:45,320 --> 01:35:45,760
Maybe...

1083
01:35:46,160 --> 01:35:48,800
I thought you might know something.

1084
01:35:49,240 --> 01:35:51,440
I think you should tell
Mercan to put her mind at ease.

1085
01:35:51,880 --> 01:35:55,160
The Ateş I know would never hurt Mercan.

1086
01:36:02,400 --> 01:36:04,200
Taking a break was a good idea.

1087
01:36:06,360 --> 01:36:08,320
I can never say no to coffee.

1088
01:36:11,160 --> 01:36:13,040
Tea is life.

1089
01:36:14,040 --> 01:36:16,960
I think coffee is life.

1090
01:36:18,920 --> 01:36:22,440
You high society people probably
eat menemen without onions.

1091
01:36:23,400 --> 01:36:25,239
For all I know, maybe you
don’t eat menemen at all.

1092
01:36:25,240 --> 01:36:26,320
I don’t know that either.

1093
01:36:28,080 --> 01:36:30,680
The sentence you just made...

1094
01:36:31,360 --> 01:36:33,280
falls apart whichever way you look at it.

1095
01:36:35,000 --> 01:36:37,280
First of all, I’m not high society.

1096
01:36:37,840 --> 01:36:39,600
Second, I eat menemen.

1097
01:36:39,920 --> 01:36:40,960
And I like it very much.

1098
01:36:42,040 --> 01:36:44,320
Besides, menemen is made
without onions, Cemal.

1099
01:36:44,640 --> 01:36:46,960
Fine, Demet. Then you can eat
your menemen without onions.

1100
01:37:00,320 --> 01:37:03,320
Things are quite busy
at the company these days.

1101
01:37:04,160 --> 01:37:05,160
Of course.

1102
01:37:05,480 --> 01:37:10,680
While reading this month’s reports I was...

1103
01:37:12,400 --> 01:37:13,400
quite exhausted.

1104
01:37:14,280 --> 01:37:15,280
Don’t even ask.

1105
01:37:16,160 --> 01:37:17,160
We’re very tired.

1106
01:37:18,560 --> 01:37:21,520
So I think we can switch
to relaxation mode now.

1107
01:37:21,840 --> 01:37:22,840
Right?

1108
01:37:31,800 --> 01:37:32,240
Well...

1109
01:37:32,640 --> 01:37:36,000
I was going to tell you something...
I owed you something, didn’t I?

1110
01:37:36,920 --> 01:37:37,920
What debt?

1111
01:37:38,560 --> 01:37:40,960
You remember I told you...

1112
01:37:41,080 --> 01:37:42,320
once we finish these matters...

1113
01:37:44,200 --> 01:37:45,480
I would treat you to dinner.

1114
01:37:46,960 --> 01:37:49,120
That was left hanging
and it keeps bothering me.

1115
01:37:50,720 --> 01:37:52,320
Oh yes.

1116
01:37:53,280 --> 01:37:54,280
It was left hanging.

1117
01:37:54,760 --> 01:37:57,160
So I was thinking... if
you’re free tomorrow...

1118
01:37:58,520 --> 01:37:59,760
It doesn’t have to be tomorrow.

1119
01:37:59,920 --> 01:38:01,080
Whenever you’re available.

1120
01:38:02,160 --> 01:38:03,320
I’ll take you out for dinner.

1121
01:38:04,080 --> 01:38:05,320
I gave my word.

1122
01:38:06,080 --> 01:38:07,480
It wouldn’t be right otherwise.

1123
01:38:12,120 --> 01:38:13,160
Alright.

1124
01:38:14,960 --> 01:38:15,960
Alright.

1125
01:38:16,760 --> 01:38:17,760
Why not?

1126
01:38:17,800 --> 01:38:19,640
Super, super. I’m very happy.

1127
01:39:01,800 --> 01:39:03,400
Hasn’t this sulking gone on long enough?

1128
01:39:08,280 --> 01:39:10,280
Please stop acting like a child, Berat.

1129
01:39:17,480 --> 01:39:19,400
Unfortunately I can’t help it.

1130
01:39:23,400 --> 01:39:24,680
I’m a child by nature.

1131
01:39:27,240 --> 01:39:29,040
Whatever I do turns out
childish, doesn’t it?

1132
01:39:29,120 --> 01:39:30,120
That’s why.

1133
01:39:36,760 --> 01:39:38,520
Look, I know you’re hurt.

1134
01:39:39,720 --> 01:39:41,440
But you misunderstood me.

1135
01:39:45,520 --> 01:39:47,960
The issue is not that you
wouldn’t be a good father.

1136
01:39:49,120 --> 01:39:50,160
It’s my fears.

1137
01:39:54,880 --> 01:39:57,200
That’s not right, Zehra.

1138
01:39:59,560 --> 01:40:00,720
You don’t want a child.

1139
01:40:03,680 --> 01:40:05,440
You don’t trust me.

1140
01:40:13,280 --> 01:40:14,680
You...

1141
01:40:14,880 --> 01:40:17,280
In this mansion you grew
up with your mother’s...

1142
01:40:18,480 --> 01:40:22,600
love and compassion.

1143
01:40:23,400 --> 01:40:24,800
You don’t understand my feelings.

1144
01:40:31,160 --> 01:40:32,160
Didn’t your mother...

1145
01:40:34,520 --> 01:40:35,520
love you?

1146
01:40:37,280 --> 01:40:39,480
What kind of childhood did you have?

1147
01:40:47,200 --> 01:40:50,200
To have a childhood, one
must first be a child, Berat.

1148
01:40:55,320 --> 01:40:57,800
The wound has scarred over, let it be.

1149
01:41:13,600 --> 01:41:17,120
What is the secret you even hide from me?

1150
01:41:19,560 --> 01:41:23,120
Whenever something about your family
is mentioned your eyes fill with tears.

1151
01:41:41,160 --> 01:41:43,400
Look, this one is nice. What do you say?

1152
01:41:54,120 --> 01:41:57,680
This one is nicer, very simple.
I think we should choose this one.

1153
01:41:59,400 --> 01:42:00,400
You think so?

1154
01:42:02,520 --> 01:42:03,520
Alright.

1155
01:42:04,120 --> 01:42:05,680
I suppose it didn’t quite win you over.

1156
01:42:08,000 --> 01:42:15,520
Whichever one makes your eyes shine with
joy... that will be the right choice for us.

1157
01:42:16,120 --> 01:42:17,960
Let’s order the invitations you like.

1158
01:42:20,840 --> 01:42:22,080
What are you thinking about?

1159
01:42:24,840 --> 01:42:26,760
I want to ask you something.

1160
01:42:27,240 --> 01:42:28,240
Go ahead.

1161
01:42:29,480 --> 01:42:31,080
Who is this Mrs. Sibel?

1162
01:42:32,160 --> 01:42:33,160
Mrs. Sibel?

1163
01:42:33,960 --> 01:42:35,280
The one you spoke with earlier.

1164
01:42:36,320 --> 01:42:37,320
Oh.

1165
01:42:37,840 --> 01:42:38,840
Work.

1166
01:42:39,520 --> 01:42:40,520
Work?

1167
01:42:41,600 --> 01:42:45,200
All day there’s talk about work,
but what kind of work is it exactly?

1168
01:42:45,920 --> 01:42:47,880
One thing is certain,
there is some kind of work.

1169
01:42:49,440 --> 01:42:50,840
You’re getting more and more tense.

1170
01:42:51,520 --> 01:42:52,520
Maybe.

1171
01:42:53,400 --> 01:42:55,840
I wish we had never gotten
into all this wedding business.

1172
01:42:56,760 --> 01:42:58,840
Look, I said work and
it irritated me again.

1173
01:43:02,800 --> 01:43:03,800
Don’t get irritated.

1174
01:43:05,000 --> 01:43:06,000
This wedding will happen.

1175
01:43:06,720 --> 01:43:09,040
Everything that belongs
in a wedding will be there.

1176
01:43:09,800 --> 01:43:11,160
Everything will be complete.

1177
01:43:11,440 --> 01:43:12,560
The very best of everything.

1178
01:43:17,040 --> 01:43:19,440
As long as you are beside me,
everything is complete for me.

1179
01:43:20,840 --> 01:43:22,200
I need nothing else.

1180
01:43:25,400 --> 01:43:26,640
The same for me.

1181
01:43:27,920 --> 01:43:29,400
We are two halves of the same apple.

1182
01:43:30,920 --> 01:43:33,520
If one of us is missing,
the other is incomplete.

1183
01:43:33,920 --> 01:43:35,560
But our traditions are important as well.

1184
01:43:36,880 --> 01:43:39,960
Everything must be exactly
as my wife wants. Understood?

1185
01:43:42,280 --> 01:43:44,680
Now that we’ve settled the
invitations, I’ll be off.

1186
01:43:45,520 --> 01:43:46,520
Where to?

1187
01:43:46,880 --> 01:43:48,360
We said we would go out tonight.

1188
01:43:50,920 --> 01:43:51,920
It’s already evening.

1189
01:43:53,400 --> 01:43:54,840
Why are you so curious?

1190
01:43:55,960 --> 01:43:57,480
I’m not curious at all.

1191
01:43:58,040 --> 01:44:01,520
When you keep saying
work, naturally people ask.

1192
01:44:02,360 --> 01:44:03,800
Otherwise go wherever you’re going.

1193
01:44:04,720 --> 01:44:07,440
Alright, it’s good you’re leaving.
I’ll take care of my own matters.

1194
01:44:07,960 --> 01:44:08,960
Alright.

1195
01:44:09,520 --> 01:44:12,720
I was about to say you could
come with me if you wanted.

1196
01:44:13,120 --> 01:44:15,560
But you’re right, everyone
should mind their own business.

1197
01:44:16,720 --> 01:44:17,720
No, no.

1198
01:44:18,040 --> 01:44:21,400
There’s no need anyway.
I said I couldn’t come.

1199
01:44:21,760 --> 01:44:23,200
Alright then, I’m leaving.

1200
01:44:29,600 --> 01:44:32,320
Your mysterious behavior is
starting to get on my nerves.

1201
01:44:33,800 --> 01:44:35,280
But there’s only one way to find out.

1202
01:45:13,080 --> 01:45:15,400
What is it, Mother? Why
did you call me again?

1203
01:45:22,800 --> 01:45:26,640
I thought we both had
already said our final words.

1204
01:45:27,680 --> 01:45:28,680
What happened?

1205
01:45:29,840 --> 01:45:33,520
My opinion on the
marriage is still the same,

1206
01:45:33,600 --> 01:45:38,000
but there's something else
I want to talk to you about

1207
01:45:40,640 --> 01:45:42,920
I shouldn't mention it,

1208
01:45:43,000 --> 01:45:44,840
but I have to.

1209
01:45:44,920 --> 01:45:47,200
You can't stay here.

1210
01:45:48,000 --> 01:45:50,920
Mom, you can't start over.

1211
01:45:51,120 --> 01:45:53,120
Just listen to me.

1212
01:45:57,360 --> 01:46:00,600
Okay, fine, go ahead. What is it?

1213
01:46:04,720 --> 01:46:05,720
Your father.

1214
01:46:10,240 --> 01:46:12,520
Your father is very ill.

1215
01:46:16,120 --> 01:46:17,120
My father is ill?

1216
01:46:18,520 --> 01:46:19,520
Yes.

1217
01:46:21,240 --> 01:46:25,800
Look, I want to build a life here.

1218
01:46:27,000 --> 01:46:28,000
I understand.

1219
01:46:28,680 --> 01:46:36,680
But I thought perhaps you would come
with me to Cairo to see your father.

1220
01:46:41,640 --> 01:46:45,520
My son, you have to make a choice.

1221
01:46:46,840 --> 01:46:52,440
Your father on his deathbed, or Çiçek?

1222
01:47:49,760 --> 01:47:51,280
What is this place?

1223
01:47:52,360 --> 01:47:56,560
He said work and came here. So he lied.

1224
01:47:58,080 --> 01:47:59,760
But it was obvious he was up to something.

1225
01:48:13,320 --> 01:48:17,520
What are you doing here?
Were you following me?

1226
01:48:19,720 --> 01:48:25,319
Well, I followed you because...

1227
01:48:25,320 --> 01:48:27,240
Because you were curious where I was going.

1228
01:48:29,960 --> 01:48:33,520
You kept saying work.
Good thing I came, look.

1229
01:48:33,920 --> 01:48:35,440
Your lie is out in the open.

1230
01:48:35,880 --> 01:48:37,399
What does this place have to do with work?

1231
01:48:37,400 --> 01:48:39,360
Weren’t you going to meet Mrs. Sibel?

1232
01:48:40,000 --> 01:48:42,240
You’ll understand soon enough
what it has to do with it.

1233
01:48:42,640 --> 01:48:45,360
Besides, I told you that
you could come with me.

1234
01:48:46,200 --> 01:48:47,280
There is no Sibel.

1235
01:48:48,240 --> 01:48:50,640
You said it halfheartedly.
Don’t think I didn’t notice.

1236
01:48:52,760 --> 01:48:54,400
Since you came all this way...

1237
01:48:58,000 --> 01:49:00,520
let’s settle this in the ring.

1238
01:49:02,400 --> 01:49:03,440
Didn’t you have work?

1239
01:49:04,440 --> 01:49:07,880
You are my work and my business, my Mercan.

1240
01:49:09,760 --> 01:49:11,240
Are you sure you want this?

1241
01:49:12,320 --> 01:49:13,320
Yes, why?

1242
01:49:13,760 --> 01:49:17,600
I just wanted to warn you so
you wouldn’t regret it later.

1243
01:49:18,720 --> 01:49:20,960
Well, well. So you’re confident.

1244
01:49:21,920 --> 01:49:23,760
Alright then. Let the challenge begin.

1245
01:49:25,280 --> 01:49:26,320
Let the challenge begin.

1246
01:49:45,080 --> 01:49:49,520
Not long now, my Mercan.

1247
01:49:50,280 --> 01:49:53,960
We’ll leave this place
behind and be very happy.

1248
01:50:01,560 --> 01:50:02,560
Brother.

1249
01:50:09,560 --> 01:50:13,240
Brother, are you alright? Why
are you looking at me like that?

1250
01:50:14,080 --> 01:50:15,600
And you still ask, sis?

1251
01:50:16,440 --> 01:50:18,080
Why are you sneaking up like that?

1252
01:50:18,400 --> 01:50:20,240
Sneaking up?

1253
01:50:22,440 --> 01:50:26,800
That wasn’t my intention.
If I scared you, I’m sorry.

1254
01:50:37,400 --> 01:50:38,400
What are those, brother?

1255
01:50:40,880 --> 01:50:43,880
Nothing. Just my employees.

1256
01:50:44,920 --> 01:50:49,440
Come on, sis. I have a lot of
work to do. Don’t hold me up.

1257
01:50:54,000 --> 01:50:55,280
What’s wrong with him?

1258
01:51:10,680 --> 01:51:16,480
All that mysterious behavior,
disappearing. What was it for? Tell me.

1259
01:51:19,640 --> 01:51:21,680
I came to the gym, that’s
all. What’s the big deal?

1260
01:51:22,120 --> 01:51:24,760
If I hadn’t followed you, I
wouldn’t even know you came here.

1261
01:51:27,160 --> 01:51:31,560
But I knew you would
follow me. My detective wife.

1262
01:51:32,200 --> 01:51:35,280
So you knew. You knew all along.

1263
01:51:37,160 --> 01:51:41,080
Yes. As surely as I know my own name.

1264
01:51:41,640 --> 01:51:44,560
I don’t understand why you
had to create so much curiosity.

1265
01:51:55,920 --> 01:51:59,120
Maybe I like the fact that
you’re curious about me.

1266
01:52:10,200 --> 01:52:12,000
Besides, there are still
things I don’t know.

1267
01:52:14,880 --> 01:52:16,079
Such as?

1268
01:52:16,080 --> 01:52:19,120
Where did you go after
breakfast? Who is Mrs. Sibel?

1269
01:52:21,760 --> 01:52:23,000
Am I obliged to tell you?

1270
01:52:23,760 --> 01:52:26,360
Of course you are.

1271
01:52:28,040 --> 01:52:31,680
There were supposed to be no secrets between
us. We wouldn’t hide anything from each other.

1272
01:52:32,120 --> 01:52:33,120
Did we say that?

1273
01:52:35,840 --> 01:52:40,840
Marriage needs a little mystery. To keep love
alive, the excitement must stay alive too.

1274
01:52:42,120 --> 01:52:44,480
This is good then. For Sibel as well.

1275
01:52:46,640 --> 01:52:49,600
If you cheat on me, this
is the answer you will get.

1276
01:52:52,400 --> 01:52:54,056
You’ll hold that over my
head forever, won’t you?

1277
01:52:54,080 --> 01:52:55,800
Until the very end. Gladly.

1278
01:52:57,160 --> 01:53:01,400
I accept it. Because some
defeats bring happiness.

1279
01:53:01,960 --> 01:53:04,480
Like a defeat that comes
from the one you love.

1280
01:53:05,840 --> 01:53:11,440
Is that so? Then wait a little.
I’m about to make you very happy.

1281
01:53:13,480 --> 01:53:15,400
I’m going to win this match.

1282
01:53:20,560 --> 01:53:24,520
If my opponent is you, I’m willing to lose.

1283
01:53:27,040 --> 01:53:31,800
Oh please. You saw the challenge and
started looking for an excuse to surrender.

1284
01:53:34,360 --> 01:53:36,440
Surrender is not always defeat.

1285
01:53:37,680 --> 01:53:38,680
Then what is it?

1286
01:53:39,160 --> 01:53:42,640
If you lose to the one
you love, it is victory.

1287
01:53:43,600 --> 01:53:46,440
Besides, love is a game
where both players win.

1288
01:53:47,440 --> 01:53:49,800
So you’re saying love always wins.

1289
01:53:50,680 --> 01:53:57,480
Yes, I am saying that. Because
love listens to no one and nothing.

1290
01:53:58,760 --> 01:54:00,400
We learned that by living through it.

1291
01:54:01,440 --> 01:54:05,760
Last week we were divorcing.
Now we’re together.

1292
01:54:11,480 --> 01:54:14,720
I’m glad we’re here.
I’m glad we’re together.

1293
01:54:16,440 --> 01:54:17,720
Don’t ever leave me.

1294
01:54:26,080 --> 01:54:27,160
But I might leave you.

1295
01:54:27,960 --> 01:54:30,400
That would be difficult. Even
if you wanted to, you couldn’t.

1296
01:54:39,040 --> 01:54:40,320
Your reflexes are good.

1297
01:54:41,040 --> 01:54:42,640
You’re starting a war, just so you know.

1298
01:54:46,440 --> 01:54:47,760
Don’t you know love is a war?

1299
01:54:59,400 --> 01:55:02,360
That was a strong hit.
I was going easy on you.

1300
01:55:03,680 --> 01:55:07,360
If you’re playing this rough,
the match is only beginning for me.

1301
01:55:08,360 --> 01:55:12,080
You’re too late. I’m
about to knock you out.

1302
01:55:19,560 --> 01:55:23,560
It’s not that easy.
Why are you so determined?

1303
01:55:24,440 --> 01:55:27,840
Could it be because you canceled
today’s appointment, sir?

1304
01:55:29,680 --> 01:55:32,320
If I didn’t have an important
matter, I wouldn’t have canceled it.

1305
01:55:32,920 --> 01:55:35,840
If you keep this up, we won’t
finish the wedding preparations.

1306
01:55:36,600 --> 01:55:37,200
We will.

1307
01:55:37,600 --> 01:55:38,600
How?

1308
01:55:40,160 --> 01:55:42,840
Mrs. Sibel from the event
company will come to the mansion.

1309
01:55:45,240 --> 01:55:47,000
She will make a special
presentation for us.

1310
01:55:53,400 --> 01:55:57,400
Was this the important matter
you spoke of? Was this it?

1311
01:56:00,240 --> 01:56:02,720
Yes. The most important matter of my life.

1312
01:56:04,280 --> 01:56:09,119
Why did you hide it? You’re unbelievable.
Never hide something like this again.

1313
01:56:09,120 --> 01:56:10,960
The things that crossed my mind.

1314
01:56:11,960 --> 01:56:12,960
Were you jealous?

1315
01:56:15,840 --> 01:56:19,400
You haven’t seen anything yet.
I wouldn’t recommend it either.

1316
01:56:23,120 --> 01:56:26,080
If we feared iron, we wouldn’t
board a train, Ms. Mercan.

1317
01:56:42,320 --> 01:56:44,040
I told you I would knock you out.

1318
01:56:55,720 --> 01:56:58,000
I’m willing to lose to you forever.

1319
01:57:03,440 --> 01:57:11,440
And you, Mercan Karahan?
Will you be my forever?

1320
01:59:32,680 --> 01:59:34,680
Ateş.

1321
01:59:38,680 --> 01:59:40,679
I found you.

1322
01:59:40,680 --> 01:59:42,680
Here you are.

1323
01:59:52,680 --> 01:59:54,679
I worried so much about you.

1324
01:59:54,680 --> 01:59:56,680
Worrried so much...

1325
02:00:00,680 --> 02:00:02,720
I knew you were not well
from the ache in my heart.

1326
02:00:08,680 --> 02:00:10,679
But look, I am here.

1327
02:00:10,680 --> 02:00:12,680
I am with you.

1328
02:00:18,680 --> 02:00:20,680
Come on, open your eyes.

1329
02:00:24,640 --> 02:00:26,639
Look at me.

1330
02:00:26,640 --> 02:00:28,640
Look into my eyes.

1331
02:00:39,920 --> 02:00:41,960
You cannot leave me alone.

1332
02:01:04,920 --> 02:01:06,080
Come on, get up.

1333
02:01:07,520 --> 02:01:08,720
Take my hand.

1334
02:01:12,320 --> 02:01:14,200
Let us get out of here together.

1335
02:01:24,640 --> 02:01:26,640
Let us go on with our lives hand in hand.

1336
02:01:37,920 --> 02:01:39,080
Mercan...

1337
02:01:40,640 --> 02:01:42,640
Is that you?

1338
02:02:14,120 --> 02:02:15,120
Ateş.

1339
02:02:19,920 --> 02:02:21,360
Come on.

1340
02:02:22,680 --> 02:02:24,680
Where are you? I'm waiting.

1341
02:02:37,920 --> 02:02:38,920
Ateş.

1342
02:02:41,920 --> 02:02:43,760
I'm waiting for you?

1343
02:02:45,920 --> 02:02:47,680
Come on.

1344
02:02:47,920 --> 02:02:50,040
I'm waiting for you?

1345
02:02:57,120 --> 02:02:58,360
Come on.

1346
02:03:00,720 --> 02:03:02,040
Ateş.

1347
02:03:02,320 --> 02:03:04,560
Come on, I'm waiting.

1348
02:04:29,520 --> 02:04:30,760
Where were you?

1349
02:04:31,440 --> 02:04:33,040
I worried so much.

1350
02:04:33,520 --> 02:04:35,880
I have been waiting here for so long.

1351
02:05:00,120 --> 02:05:01,440
This feeling...

1352
02:05:10,720 --> 02:05:11,720
Is it real?

1353
02:05:14,120 --> 02:05:15,160
It is.

1354
02:05:16,880 --> 02:05:19,360
Nothing ever been more real.

1355
02:05:29,120 --> 02:05:30,440
You are here.

1356
02:05:32,720 --> 02:05:34,440
I am.

1357
02:05:35,920 --> 02:05:38,160
I knew you would come.

1358
02:05:39,720 --> 02:05:40,960
How did you?

1359
02:05:43,120 --> 02:05:44,760
Because you always came.

1360
02:05:46,440 --> 02:05:50,439
And I never stopped waiting.

1361
02:05:50,440 --> 02:05:56,439
I told myself that this
story cannot end like this.

1362
02:05:56,440 --> 02:05:58,440
It won't.

1363
02:07:42,600 --> 02:07:44,600
Do it like this.

1364
02:08:09,680 --> 02:08:11,040
Let me see your wound.

1365
02:09:34,920 --> 02:09:37,800
Do as I say, naughty kitten.

1366
02:09:40,400 --> 02:09:42,320
Retract your claws once in a while.

1367
02:10:22,680 --> 02:10:24,240
You can't go anywhere.

1368
02:10:24,880 --> 02:10:27,040
I've already told you but
I guess it wasn't clear.

1369
02:10:36,440 --> 02:10:38,040
Let me help you.

1370
02:13:09,000 --> 02:13:10,800
You're such a troublemaker.

1371
02:13:46,080 --> 02:13:47,200
Thank you.

1372
02:14:10,760 --> 02:14:12,400
Thank you.

1373
02:14:41,200 --> 02:14:43,480
God, I’m grateful.

1374
02:16:32,160 --> 02:16:35,360
Stay here and don’t move.

1375
02:16:37,920 --> 02:16:40,520
Don't go!

1376
02:16:47,560 --> 02:16:49,040
What if something happens to you?

1377
02:16:49,120 --> 02:16:51,120
Don't worry. Nothing will happen.

1378
02:16:51,360 --> 02:16:53,440
I promise I’ll come back.

1379
02:16:56,560 --> 02:16:57,920
Ateş!

1380
02:17:10,600 --> 02:17:12,360
Thank God, you're safe.

1381
02:17:15,200 --> 02:17:16,560
Thank God.

1382
02:17:21,560 --> 02:17:23,040
Are you alright?

1383
02:17:26,200 --> 02:17:29,080
We're fine. I told you
to wait for me there.

1384
02:17:54,840 --> 02:17:56,120
Don't worry, I'm right here.
